 Re: Computer Singularity and ufos</span><hr size=1> Watch the very bad sci-fi movie VIRTUOSITY from 1995, with Denzel Washington and Russell Crowe.  In it a 50-terabyte computer A.I. program not only develops self-awareness, but also they use nano-bots to give him physical form.<br><br>So naturally he runs amok.  LOL<br><br>These ideas are VERY old in print SF. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/udavidrichmond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>David Richmond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/22/02 7:07:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesufos.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Computer Singularity and ufos</span><hr size=1> I think androidal evolution may be next. Androids being technologically altered people and humanistically altered technology. I saw a denzel Washington movie, but don't think it was that one. He knocked out a space monster with one punch. I think they had a master computer but where biological. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ufraterliber.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FraterLiber</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 168<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/22/02 10:32:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesufos.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Computer Singularity and ufos</span><hr size=1> Machine Intelligence is the only rational end result, eventually.  Once that happens acquired traits can be passed on to, or left out of, each generation.  This allows instant adaptation and even alteration of existing units.<br><br>No more being at the mercy of the environment.<br><br>You need to read some science fiction, there is a huge amount of it concerned with these kinds of considerations.  Asimov, Clarke, Heinlein, and so on.  Check 'em out, you'll love 'em. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesufos.showPrevMessage?topicID=154.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesufos.showNextMessage?topicID=154.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesufos.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=3><img src=http://web.ukonline.co.uk/unexplained.m/images/addreply.jpeg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesufos.emailToFriend?topicID=154.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesufos.threadControl?topicID=154.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesufos.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=154.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesufos.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=154.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub16.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td>